A one-time Senator representing Rivers South-East senatorial district of Rivers State in the National Assembly, Senator Magnus Ngei Abe, has formally declared his interest to contest for the 2023 governorship election in Rivers State. Abe, who disclosed this on Saturday during the inauguration of Bola Ahmed Tinubu Vanguard for Ward 4, 5 and 6 in Gokana local government area of the State, said he will contest on the platform of the All Progressives Congress (APC). With his formal declaration, the former lawmaker will join other 11 governorship aspirants who will contest for the APC governorship ticket during the partyâ€™s primaries slated for May 2022. The APC chieftain stated that he would support anyone who emerges APC gubernatorial candidate in a free, fair and equitable contest. Abe added that anything short of a free, fair and equitable contest will not be accepted.